arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Single ashlar bench (?) in the west of the hypocaust room

Locus 103 is the single large ashlar against Locus 76 in the hypocaust room. This large hewn sandstone ashlar abuts Locus 76 to the west and Locus 102 to the north and east. It appears to continue below the level of Locus 102, and may rest on the main floor of the hypocaust room, presumably below the raised floor. The function of this ashlar is quite unclear, though it could possible serve as a bench (it would, however, be quite a low bench, only 20 cm above the level of the raised floor). Because of its association with Locus 102, this ashlar is phased to Stage 4.
1.30 m north south -by- 0.54 m east west.
